00:45:59.380 --> 00:46:05.863
Believe God and write your list down and tithe and give and show God that you're serious about him and be all in.

00:46:05.863 --> 00:46:09.189
Don't say, 'Well, when times get bad, Lord, here I am.

00:46:16.160 --> 00:46:16.330
You know, I just want to let you know, Lord, I'm on your side.

00:46:16.330 --> 00:46:19.520
' Whenever you see everybody dying around you, I'm all in before the storm comes.

00:46:19.520 --> 00:46:22.144
I'm not a fair-weather Christian.

00:46:26.640 --> 00:46:26.844
When times are good, I'm out partying.

00:46:28.760 --> 00:46:35.760
But when times are bad, a thousand fall at my side, ten thousand at my right hand, 'We better pray and take communion, honey.

00:46:35.760 --> 00:46:37.399
' Seriously, I'm not that way with God.

00:46:37.399 --> 00:46:43.839
I told God, 'I want you to know, man, you search me and know me.

00:47:01.320 --> 00:47:01.627
You know my heart.

00:47:01.627 --> 00:47:08.160
I'm not rotten at the core.

00:47:08.160 --> 00:47:13.346
I may have a bad day, but I don't stay in that bad day.

00:47:13.346 --> 00:47:16.302
' I don't stay in the bad day.

00:47:16.302 --> 00:47:24.800
I choose to follow Jesus in good and in bad, on the mountain or in the valley.

00:47:24.800 --> 00:47:26.571
Do you understand?

00:47:26.571 --> 00:47:32.457
God's still God, and he's God on the mountain and he's God in the valley.

00:47:42.880 --> 00:47:43.306
I love that song.

